    "body": "Fixes #1410.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\n\r\nWhen dark mode is enabled, rotating to landscape orientation while editing should retain dark mode. We did this by disabling full-screen keyboard (`android:imeOptions=\"flagNoExtractUi\"`) and hiding toolbar for landscape mode in phones. \r\n\r\n**Before:**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42454301/124658653-05cea980-de72-11eb-8f8b-0a9fec888ba7.mp4\r\n\r\n**After:**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/195721/130622851-e273e4b6-6673-4e57-ab55-e2bd2e293b99.mp4\r\n\r\n### Test\r\n\r\n1. Go to settings and enable dark mode\r\n2. Tap on a new note or a note from the notes list\r\n3. Start typing on the note\r\n4. Rotate the phone to landscape mode\r\n5. The tabs and toolbar should hide and the background of the text editor should remain dark\r\n6. Rotate the phone again\r\n7. The tabs and toolbar should be shown again\r\n8. Rotate the phone to landscape mode\r\n9. The tabs and toolbar should hide and the background of the text editor should remain dark\r\n10. Hide the keyboard\r\n11. The tabs and toolbar should be shown again\r\n12. Disable markdown\r\n13. Rotate the phone to landscape mode\r\n14. Start typing on the note\r\n15. The toolbar should hide and the background of the text editor should remain dark\r\n16. Hide the keyboard\r\n17. The toolbar (not the tabs) should be shown again\r\n\r\n### Review\r\n\r\nOnly one developer and one designer are required to review these changes, but anyone can perform the review.\r\n\r\n### Release\r\n\r\n`RELEASE-NOTES.txt` was updated in 31fedccb72994eaf4110ea59f43ab3b6b6503a36 with:\r\n> Fixed editor's background color in landscape mode with dark theme\r\n",
